folder: West End Avenue & 62nd Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
West End Ave., west side, north from West 62nd to 64th Streets. (Ave. not shown; it being on the extreme right. The view shows the excavation of buildings on this side, for the enlargement of the N.Y.C.R.R. yards.

March 19, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, further northward. Building shown in the center, is on the S.W. corner of West 64th Street and West End Ave., and will also be demolished.

March 19, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: West End Avenue & 62nd Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
West End Ave., east side, (buildings thereon) south from West 65th to 62nd Streets, as viewed from the former and across that portion of the New York Central Railroad yards upon which structures recently stood.

November 25, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
